\author{eigil-rischel}
\import{macros}
\taxon{example}
\p{
  Let #{\cC} be a representable Markov category where #{\cC_\det} admits pullbacks, and consider the Eilenberg-Moore category #{\Alg(P)} of the monad #{P} on #{\cC_\det}. It contains #{\cC \cong Kl(P)} as a full subcategory. Consider the comma category #{\Alg(P) \downarrow \cC}, whose objects are tuples #{(X \in \cC, A \in \Alg(P), a: A \to PX)}. The obvious forgetful functor to #{\cC} is a fibration (with base-change given by pullbacks computed in #{\cC_\det}). In particular, it is a Markov prefibration.
}